nodes.documentation:
his is the basic wrapped Ether contract. 
ll money deposited is transformed into ERC20 tokens at the rate of 1 wei = 1 token
nodes.name: Wrapped_Ether

nodes.documentation: dev This function creates tokens equal in value to the amount sent to the contract
nodes.name: createToken

nodes.documentation:
dev This function 'unwraps' an _amount of Ether in the sender's balance by transferring 
ther to them
param _value The amount of the token to unwrap
nodes.name: withdraw

nodes.documentation:
param _owner is the owner address used to look up the balance
return Returns the balance associated with the passed in _owner
nodes.name: balanceOf

nodes.documentation:
dev Allows for a transfer of tokens to _to
param _to The address to send tokens to
param _amount The amount of tokens to send
nodes.name: transfer

nodes.documentation:
dev Allows an address with sufficient spending allowance to send tokens on the behalf of _from
param _from The address to send tokens from
param _to The address to send tokens to
param _amount The amount of tokens to send
nodes.name: transferFrom

nodes.documentation:
dev This function approves a _spender an _amount of tokens to use
param _spender address
param _amount amount the spender is being approved for
return true if spender appproved successfully
nodes.name: approve

nodes.documentation:
param _owner address
param _spender address
return Returns the remaining allowance of tokens granted to the _spender from the _owner
nodes.name: allowance

nodes.documentation:
dev Getter for the total_supply of wrapped ether
return total supply
nodes.name: totalSupply
